<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-updl58o1qUUe9l5SjfOlog" name=",_hBjKQKGOEeC6D4cw2ululQ" guid="-updl58o1qUUe9l5SjfOlog" changeDate="2011-06-28T09:57:19.867-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To carry out the classification task a description of the software tool use cases are captured, these are then analyzed&#xD;
    and evaluated to determine if&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;an erroneous output or malfunction by the software tool could result in the&#xD;
    possibility of a violation of safety related requirement allocated to a safety-related item or element. This leads to&#xD;
    the Tool Impact or TI value.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Tool Error Detection or TD value is based upon the probability of preventing or detecting that a software tool is&#xD;
    malfunctioning or producing erroneous output.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The TD and TI are then used to determine the Tool Confidence Level or TCL.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The user is advised to refer to ISO 26262, volume 11, clauses 11.4.3.1 to 11.4.3.4 for the details on the determining&#xD;
    factors&amp;nbsp;for TI, TD and TCL&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_dFE5YKGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ" name="Capture tool use cases" guid="_dFE5YKGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_e4G9QKGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ" name="Determine TI class" guid="_e4G9QKGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_iZHl4KGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ" name="Determine TD class" guid="_iZHl4KGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_kji2EKGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ" name="Determine TCL class" guid="_kji2EKGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_p8XU4KGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ" name="Document analysis" guid="_p8XU4KGpEeC6D4cw2ululQ"/>
  <purpose>To determine the SW tool classification. This is a 2 stage process whereby first the theTool Impact&amp;nbsp;(TI) and&#xD;
Tool&amp;nbsp;Error Detection levels are determined, from this the Tool Confidence Level (TCL) is derived.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
